\emph{Short-answer questions! No credit will be given for the answer
(even if it is correct) without the accompanying work.}

For a certain function \emph{$f$(x)}, the following equation holds:

\begin{align*}
\lim_{n \rightarrow \infty} \sum_{k=1}^n \frac{k}{n^2} \sqrt{1-\frac{k^2}{n^2}} = \int_0^1 f(x)\,dx.
\end{align*}

Find \emph{$f$(x)}.
